Following Dayton, OH resident David Cinelli's purchase of a CLT-A230M cordless phone from his local Best Buy, electronics manufacturer Sanyo was plunged into chaos Monday over fears that Cinelli might attempt to redeem the $40 rebate coupon that came with the phone.Executives at Sanyo—which employs more than 85,000 people worldwide—said they were initially overjoyed that someone had actually purchased one of their products.